// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P257740583" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Death Threat</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You receive a threatening text message from an anonymous source.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>{HeroName},<br><br>Your kind has no place in the city.  I have made it my duty to discourage you so-called 'rogues' from entering into my city.  I'm going to make an example of Desdemona, then you're next {HeroName}.  Villains like you never change!<br><br>Stalwart</scale></font></color><br><br>Really?  A death threat?  You're trying to do a little good, and maybe line your pockets a little, and <b>THIS<b> is the thanks you get.  You think Stalwart's on to something though.  However, instead of him making an example of you, you'll make an example of what happens to those that don't know their place.  You also happen to know right where he'll be.  Desdemona has been seen in a nearby cave system, he's likely going to track her down there.  She could probably use your help, you hear he's allied himself with some ex-Longbow agents and they tend to go a bit overboard.  This small time chump and his little band won't know what hit them."
// Answer Text :
"P4032860674" "HERO: Take down Stalwart and help Desdemona"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


