// Page RoguetoHero Text :
"P2766024517" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>A Familiar Face</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear a loud crash off in the distance.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>You notice some Nemesis soldiers run off when they see you.  They leave behind a long wooden crate that was broken open when it was dropped.  As you approach something rolls out of the remains of the crate and stops at your feet.  You reach down to examine the object only to have the grim realization that it's a human head.  Or at least a very impressive mechanical duplicate of one.  Turning the automaton head over in your hands you notice that this was intended to be a duplicate of the ex-villain Stardusk.  You search the crate for additional clues and discover a note with instructions to bring this crate to a nearby sewer entrace as the Stardusk automaton needs to be synched up with the real Desdemona who is being held dostage at the very same location.</scale></font></color><br><br>While you were really hoping you weren't going to have to resort to 'dashing heroics' today, it appears that you really don't have much choice.  If Nemesis is able to replace Paragon's refugees from the Rogue Isles, he could command them to do some pretty awful things."
// Answer Text :
"P2130474142" "HERO: Stop Nemesis Plot!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
